17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) is best suited for AWS developers, teams already in AWS ecosystem, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Devin, meanwhile, shines for teams wanting autonomous coding agents, complex multi step tasks, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer) describes itself as \"AI coding companion optimized for AWS development.\" Devin, established in 2023, positions itself as \"The first fully autonomous AI software engineer.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
18:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer)** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 8), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Devin is a poor choice — far from it. Devin excels in its own right, particularly for teams wanting autonomous coding agents and complex multi step tasks.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value free tier for individuals, go with Amazon CodeWhisperer (Q Developer). If can work autonomously on tasks matters more to you, Devin is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
